{
    "level": "A1",
    "intro": "In this topic you will learn to choose between <strong>this, that, these, those</strong> using the ideas of <strong>near / far</strong> and <strong>singular / plural</strong>.",
    "rules": [
        {
            "label": "NEAR + SINGULAR",
            "color": "emerald",
            "text": "<strong>This</strong> refers to one thing near the speaker:",
            "example": "This book is mine."
        },
        {
            "label": "FAR + SINGULAR",
            "color": "blue",
            "text": "<strong>That</strong> refers to one thing farther away:",
            "example": "That car is expensive."
        },
        {
            "label": "PLURAL",
            "color": "amber",
            "text": "<strong>These / those</strong> are the plural forms: near or far.",
            "example": "These shoes are new. / Those houses are old."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "1. Quick chart",
    "intro": "Combine distance and number to choose the correct demonstrative.",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Near + singular",
            "title": "this",
            "subtitle": "this bag, this idea, this one"
        },
        {
            "label": "Far + singular",
            "title": "that",
            "subtitle": "that bag, that idea, that one"
        },
        {
            "label": "Near + plural",
            "title": "these",
            "subtitle": "these bags, these ideas, these ones"
        },
        {
            "label": "Far + plural",
            "title": "those",
            "subtitle": "those bags, those ideas, those ones"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "2. Main uses",
    "sections": [
        {
            "label": "Near or far",
            "color": "emerald",
            "description": "Demonstratives often show <strong>where</strong> a thing or idea is in relation to the speaker.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This chair is comfortable.",
                    "ua": "This chair is comfortable."
                },
                {
                    "en": "That building is very old.",
                    "ua": "That building is very old."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Those lights look beautiful at night.",
                    "ua": "Those lights look beautiful at night."
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Singular and plural",
            "color": "blue",
            "description": "The form depends on both distance and number.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This apple is sweet, but these apples are sour.",
                    "ua": "This apple is sweet, but these apples are sour."
                },
                {
                    "en": "That photo is blurry, and those photos are darker.",
                    "ua": "That photo is blurry, and those photos are darker."
                },
                {
                    "en": "Who is that? Who are those people?",
                    "ua": "Who is that? Who are those people?"
                }
            ]
        },
        {
            "label": "Common patterns",
            "color": "amber",
            "description": "A demonstrative is often followed by a <strong>noun</strong>, but it can also stand alone.",
            "examples": [
                {
                    "en": "This book is easier than that one.",
                    "ua": "This book is easier than that one."
                },
                {
                    "en": "These are my keys.",
                    "ua": "These are my keys."
                },
                {
                    "en": "I do not like those.",
                    "ua": "I do not like those."
                }
            ],
            "note": "This / that go with singular nouns; these / those go with plural nouns."
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "3. Common mistakes",
    "items": [
        {
            "label": "Mistake 1",
            "color": "rose",
            "title": "Using this with a plural noun.",
            "wrong": "This shoes are new.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">These shoes are new.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Mistake 2",
            "color": "amber",
            "title": "Wrong match between that / those and the verb.",
            "wrong": "That are my keys.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">Those are my keys.</span> / <span class=\"font-mono\">That is my key.</span>"
        },
        {
            "label": "Mistake 3",
            "color": "sky",
            "title": "Mixing up one and ones.",
            "wrong": "I like this ones.",
            "right": "✅ <span class=\"font-mono\">I like these ones.</span> / <span class=\"font-mono\">I like this one.</span>"
        }
    ]
}

{
    "title": "4. Quick summary",
    "items": [
        "<strong>This</strong> = near + singular.",
        "<strong>That</strong> = far + singular.",
        "<strong>These</strong> = near + plural.",
        "<strong>Those</strong> = far + plural.",
        "A demonstrative can stand before a noun or alone: <em>this book</em>, <em>those</em>."
    ]
}

